This vendored subset keeps project notices and source-level modifications
documented in `UPSTREAM.md` and `manifest.json`.

Two upstream build-metadata files are changed by the documented patch
`patches/0001-reproducible-build-metadata.patch`: the core POM receives a fixed
manifest date and stops reading the enclosing repository, and a deterministic
`git.properties` records the pinned LanguageTool 6.8 identity. All other
included upstream files are unmodified copies from the LanguageTool 6.8 release
commit. The stdio bridge, Maven wrapper, and scripts are separate project-authored
files listed in `manifest.json`.

Polish dictionary resources carry their own preserved notices at
`sources/languagetool-language-modules/pl/src/main/resources/org/languagetool/resource/pl/README.txt`
and `sources/languagetool-language-modules/pl/src/main/resources/org/languagetool/resource/pl/hunspell/README_en.txt`.
Their license expressions are recorded separately in `manifest.json` rather
than being represented as LGPL-only.
